<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870728-0037 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Interpublic Group of Cos.</HL><DD> 07/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> IPGEARNINGS (ERN) </IN><TEXT>   Interpublic Group of Cos. reported that second-quarter profit rose 12% to $20.3 million, or 92 cents a share, from $18.1 million, or 82 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 16% to $249.5 million from $215.3 million. The New York-based advertising agency holding company attributed the higher earnings to net new business of about $352 million world-wide, a weaker U.S. dollar and overall performance of the company's international operations. Net income for the six months increased 15% to $25.7 million, or $1.17 a share, as revenue rose 18% to $452.1 million. Interpublic said its financial condition continues to be &quot;excellent,&quot; and its ability to gain new business in the first half indicates solid growth for the balance of 1987. </TEXT></DOC>